Paladin Jumps as Buyout Firm Says Transaction May Move Prices

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-15T08:45:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/paladin-jumps-as-buyout-firm-says-transaction-may-move-prices.html
Paladin Capital Ltd. (PLD) , the South
African private equity company controlled by PSG Group Ltd.,
headed for the highest closing level in a week after saying it
is considering transactions that may affect its share price.  The stock rallied for a second day, gaining 10 cents, or
3.7 percent, to 2.80 rand by 10:11 a.m. in Johannesburg.  The company made the statement in a regulatory filing
today. Paladin held 307.5 million rand ($45 million) in cash and
equivalents by Feb. 28, it said in an April 13 statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
